**Overall meaning:**

The head is made of mass upwards, the feet downwards also. On the sides is the placement of the hands, and in the middle is characterized by the belly. 

**Explanation:**

This verse provides a description of the human body, highlighting its basic structure and proportions. It can be interpreted as a simple anatomical description, but it also has a symbolic meaning that relates to the interconnectedness of the human being. 

The verse states that the head is positioned upwards, representing the realm of thought and intellect. The feet, located downwards, represent the physical and grounded aspect of the body. 

The hands, placed on the sides, symbolize action and interaction with the world. The belly, located in the middle, represents the center of the body and its vital functions.

By describing the body in this way, the verse emphasizes the balance and harmony of its different parts, as well as their interconnectedness. It suggests that each part plays a crucial role in the functioning of the whole. 


